# Code Conventions

## Components

- Functional components + hooks ONLY (no class components)
- Props interface: `{ComponentName}Props`
- Named exports only (no default exports)
- Colocated tests: `ComponentName.test.tsx`

## TypeScript

- Strict mode — no `any`, no `@ts-ignore`
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for simple types
- Import types: `import type { X } from "..."`

## Files

- kebab-case for files: `element-utils.ts`
- PascalCase for components: `LayerUI.tsx`

## How to verify
- Search changed files for class components (`extends React.Component` or `class ... extends Component`) and confirm none were introduced.
- Search changed files for `export default` and confirm only named exports are used.
- Confirm `.ts` utility filenames use kebab-case (for example, `element-utils.ts`).
- Confirm `.tsx` component filenames use PascalCase (for example, `LayerUI.tsx`).
- Confirm new/updated components use `{ComponentName}Props` naming for props types.
- Confirm type-only imports use `import type { ... } from "..."` where applicable.
